1
00:00:01,160 --> 00:00:01,960
Hey, Zen!

2
00:00:04,100 --> 00:00:06,050
-What? Are you mad?
-No, I'm not.

3
00:00:06,070 --> 00:00:07,460
You're mad.

4
00:00:08,250 --> 00:00:08,970
What?

5
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:13,730
Are you jealous?

6
00:00:13,940 --> 00:00:15,920
Huh? No way.

7
00:00:15,950 --> 00:00:16,880
You totally are.

8
00:00:17,650 --> 00:00:19,250
Is it because I had a good time

9
00:00:19,350 --> 00:00:21,160
chatting with those girls?

10
00:00:21,370 --> 00:00:22,300
What do you mean?

11
00:00:22,680 --> 00:00:24,680
Well, to be honest,

12
00:00:26,050 --> 00:00:27,980
I didn't expect you to get jealous.

13
00:00:28,820 --> 00:00:31,200
I'm just petty, alright?

14
00:00:31,820 --> 00:00:32,820
I'm heading home.

15
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:35,080
I was wrong!

16
00:00:35,550 --> 00:00:36,900
I'm not mad at you.

17
00:00:36,920 --> 00:00:37,650
Eh?

18
00:00:38,660 --> 00:00:39,260
I...

19
00:00:40,710 --> 00:00:42,930
I didn't even know
what kind of music you like.

20
00:00:42,930 --> 00:00:43,510
Well,

21
00:00:43,540 --> 00:00:45,020
that's no big deal.

22
00:00:45,480 --> 00:00:46,220
I...

23
00:00:48,020 --> 00:00:50,950
I thought I'd be fine
no matter who you got along with.

24
00:00:52,860 --> 00:00:54,520
You're friendly to everyone.

25
00:00:55,840 --> 00:00:57,470
You really know how to win people over.

26
00:00:57,470 --> 00:00:59,310
See? You really are mad at me.

27
00:00:59,340 --> 00:01:00,240
No!

28
00:01:00,380 --> 00:01:01,560
I just think...

29
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:04,860
it's embarrassing that I still get jealous

30
00:01:04,860 --> 00:01:06,950
over something this trivial and can't

31
00:01:06,950 --> 00:01:09,010
even keep my emotions under control.

32
00:01:12,730 --> 00:01:14,140
Let's just call it a day.

33
00:01:15,130 --> 00:01:16,730
I'll calm down after a while.

34
00:01:19,240 --> 00:01:21,300
How could I possibly leave you alone?

35
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:51,360
Let's plan

36
00:01:51,910 --> 00:01:53,960
our next date more carefully.

37
00:01:54,690 --> 00:01:55,380
Date?

38
00:01:56,850 --> 00:01:59,009
Still, it was really fun.

39
00:01:59,950 --> 00:02:01,340
Making plans,

40
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:03,090
meeting up,

41
00:02:03,900 --> 00:02:06,000
and going somewhere together—
things like that.

42
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,110
Sorry for ruining our date.

43
00:02:08,139 --> 00:02:09,550
No, no.

44
00:02:09,580 --> 00:02:11,440
I'm not talking about today's concert.

45
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:12,470
I know.

46
00:02:12,490 --> 00:02:13,490
I was just joking.

47
00:02:14,630 --> 00:02:16,060
Geez.

48
00:02:17,340 --> 00:02:19,200
Then, let's go on a date somewhere

49
00:02:19,220 --> 00:02:19,930
next time.

50
00:02:21,640 --> 00:02:23,390
Mm, let's.

51
00:02:24,150 --> 00:02:25,490
Maybe we should just take a trip overseas.

52
00:02:25,490 --> 00:02:27,040
Don't be silly.

53
00:02:27,190 --> 00:02:30,040
With our schedules, we can barely
manage a trip within the country.

54
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:32,250
You've got projects
on your plate too, right?

55
00:02:32,250 --> 00:02:33,470
Yeah, true.

56
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:37,860
At most, we could probably
manage one night.

57
00:02:38,420 --> 00:02:39,060
Well,

58
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:40,130
isn't that nice?

59
00:02:40,770 --> 00:02:43,829
Doing things like that
when we've just started dating.

60
00:02:44,079 --> 00:02:44,610
Yeah.

61
00:02:45,670 --> 00:02:46,470
Your birthday

62
00:02:47,090 --> 00:02:48,450
is coming up soon.

63
00:02:49,430 --> 00:02:51,690
We'll just treat it
as a birthday celebration.

64
00:02:51,690 --> 00:02:52,090
Eh?

65
00:02:53,180 --> 00:02:53,680
What?

66
00:02:53,990 --> 00:02:54,530
You...

67
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,070
You know my birthday?

68
00:02:58,220 --> 00:02:59,829
What kind of person do you think I am?

69
00:02:59,829 --> 00:03:01,760
That's exactly why I'm surprised.

70
00:03:02,670 --> 00:03:03,730
Come to think of it,

71
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:07,290
no one's ever celebrated
my birthday before.

72
00:03:08,010 --> 00:03:09,430
You haven't celebrated mine either, right?

73
00:03:09,430 --> 00:03:13,890
That's because you never gave off any vibe
that made people want to celebrate it.

74
00:03:18,410 --> 00:03:19,590
But don't worry.

75
00:03:21,300 --> 00:03:22,460
From now on,

76
00:03:23,430 --> 00:03:25,490
I'll celebrate your birthday for you.

77
00:03:25,490 --> 00:03:26,790
No need. It doesn't matter.

78
00:03:26,790 --> 00:03:28,130
I'm not a kid anymore.

79
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:29,950
But you still want to celebrate mine.

80
00:03:29,950 --> 00:03:30,910
Got a problem with that?

81
00:03:30,910 --> 00:03:31,720
Yes.

82
00:03:31,910 --> 00:03:33,570
I want to celebrate yours too.

83
00:03:35,860 --> 00:03:36,740
So,

84
00:03:37,020 --> 00:03:38,880
since we're celebrating anyway,

85
00:03:39,230 --> 00:03:42,160
let's make it a trip
to celebrate both our birthdays.

86
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:43,150
Let's find

87
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:45,010
somewhere nice to stay.

88
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:46,650
Well,

89
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:48,370
I like that idea.

90
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:49,780
It's settled then.

91
00:03:50,910 --> 00:03:52,040
Now all that's left

92
00:03:52,950 --> 00:03:55,410
is to see
whether our work schedules line up.

93
00:03:56,350 --> 00:03:57,350
I'll make it work.

94
00:03:57,980 --> 00:03:59,040
This time for sure.

95
00:04:00,820 --> 00:04:01,480
It's a deal.

96
00:04:03,020 --> 00:04:04,160
Me too.

97
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:09,110
[Development]

98
00:04:16,410 --> 00:04:17,800
Hey, Shido.

99
00:04:18,430 --> 00:04:19,750
It's been a long time.

100
00:04:21,010 --> 00:04:21,730
Futami?

101
00:05:24,140 --> 00:05:28,830
[Fake Fact Lips]

102
00:05:29,900 --> 00:05:34,290
[Episode 7: I'm Joining This Rivalry Too!]

103
00:05:35,220 --> 00:05:37,790
Futami's transfer was so sudden.

104
00:05:38,330 --> 00:05:41,040
I heard he'd be transferred back
within a few years,

105
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:43,980
but he never contacted me.
Must have been swamped.

106
00:05:44,790 --> 00:05:45,320
Oh.

107
00:05:46,060 --> 00:05:47,500
Do you two keep in touch?

108
00:05:48,220 --> 00:05:48,720
Eh?

109
00:05:49,590 --> 00:05:52,190
I told you we went to
the same college, didn't I?

110
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:52,840
Eh?

111
00:05:53,220 --> 00:05:54,390
Why are you so surprised?

112
00:05:54,390 --> 00:05:55,650
You never told me that.

113
00:05:56,060 --> 00:05:57,920
No way, I must've mentioned it.

114
00:05:57,940 --> 00:05:59,270
No, I never heard you...

115
00:06:00,780 --> 00:06:02,430
Wait, actually, maybe once.

116
00:06:02,460 --> 00:06:03,650
See?

117
00:06:03,670 --> 00:06:06,130
You really have no interest
in other people.

118
00:06:09,880 --> 00:06:10,970
However,

119
00:06:11,650 --> 00:06:13,610
now that he's back,

120
00:06:13,890 --> 00:06:15,950
things are about to get lively again.

121
00:06:16,690 --> 00:06:18,150
I've got a bad feeling he's

122
00:06:18,290 --> 00:06:20,110
going to derail our travel plans.

123
00:06:20,110 --> 00:06:22,520
Don't jinx it.

124
00:06:23,150 --> 00:06:24,460
It'll be fine.

125
00:06:24,740 --> 00:06:27,500
As long as he doesn't
get assigned to our section.

126
00:06:28,580 --> 00:06:30,720
He was in our Section 1 before.

127
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:33,409
He'll probably go back there.

128
00:06:35,630 --> 00:06:36,320
What?

129
00:06:37,140 --> 00:06:38,470
You two don't get along?

130
00:06:39,090 --> 00:06:41,130
Not many people do.

131
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:45,010
He's actually a good person, though.

132
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:02,820
I'm Futami Yuya,

133
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:04,310
transferred to Section 2

134
00:07:04,330 --> 00:07:05,620
starting today.

135
00:07:06,290 --> 00:07:08,290
I'll make full use of the skills
I learned at the Osaka branch

136
00:07:08,290 --> 00:07:09,030
and become

137
00:07:09,050 --> 00:07:11,980
a valuable member of the team
as quickly as possible.

138
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,860
I look forward to working with all of you.

139
00:07:15,570 --> 00:07:17,180
Futami, welcome aboard.

140
00:07:17,290 --> 00:07:19,550
-Looking forward to working with you.
-Mr. Futami,

141
00:07:19,550 --> 00:07:20,400
it's been a long time.

142
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:21,010
Oh!

143
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:23,040
Haven't you grown taller!

144
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:24,610
No, I'm still the same.

145
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:25,780
Why our section?

146
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:28,500
He didn't go back to Section 1!

147
00:07:29,750 --> 00:07:31,800
Is that the legendary colleague who joined
the company at the same time as you two?

148
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:32,320
Huh?

149
00:07:32,850 --> 00:07:34,040
Is he a legend now?

150
00:07:34,060 --> 00:07:34,570
Yes.

151
00:07:34,810 --> 00:07:37,940
Word is he's a standout man with
a totally different style from you two.

152
00:07:37,940 --> 00:07:38,560
Who said that?

153
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:39,540
Mr. Onishi.

154
00:07:39,909 --> 00:07:40,430
Huh?

155
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:41,900
He and Futami are close?

156
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:44,600
They seem to be each other's wingmen
at those mixers.

157
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:45,940
I see.

158
00:07:47,610 --> 00:07:50,390
Hey, Shido.

159
00:07:52,060 --> 00:07:54,460
Starting today, we're in the same section.

160
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:56,470
Once again,
looking forward to working with you.

161
00:07:55,590 --> 00:07:58,990
[Development]

162
00:07:56,860 --> 00:07:58,200
Yeah, same here.

163
00:07:59,230 --> 00:08:00,010
So cold.

164
00:08:00,550 --> 00:08:02,860
-This is what I get after all these years?
-Futami,

165
00:08:02,860 --> 00:08:04,460
last time we drank together,

166
00:08:04,470 --> 00:08:06,930
you never mentioned
you were transferring back.

167
00:08:06,930 --> 00:08:09,390
Surprise. It's a surprise.

168
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:11,720
Well, now that I see you,

169
00:08:12,250 --> 00:08:14,350
have you gotten stronger?

170
00:08:14,370 --> 00:08:15,310
No!

171
00:08:15,330 --> 00:08:18,530
We just saw each other recently.
How would I have changed?

172
00:08:19,210 --> 00:08:19,790
Hey.

173
00:08:20,530 --> 00:08:24,070
You're still the same,
with that "don’t mess with me" face.

174
00:08:24,100 --> 00:08:27,090
I don't make that face at everyone.

175
00:08:27,110 --> 00:08:27,990
Huh?

176
00:08:28,010 --> 00:08:29,070
Speaking of which,

177
00:08:29,070 --> 00:08:30,280
you two met in Osaka?

178
00:08:30,540 --> 00:08:32,470
-Mm.
-Of course.

179
00:08:33,049 --> 00:08:34,000
We're buddies

180
00:08:34,130 --> 00:08:37,789
who spent our youth together.

181
00:08:37,820 --> 00:08:39,330
Oh, really?

182
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:39,960
Ah.

183
00:08:39,980 --> 00:08:41,240
Don't grab me.

184
00:08:41,690 --> 00:08:42,429
Haha.

185
00:08:42,450 --> 00:08:42,919
Ah!

186
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:45,640
By the way,
I've heard rumors about you two.

187
00:08:46,180 --> 00:08:46,820
Something about

188
00:08:46,820 --> 00:08:51,080
the rivalry between you two sales aces
drives performance through the roof.

189
00:08:51,630 --> 00:08:52,300
Hey!

190
00:08:52,830 --> 00:08:55,020
I want in on this rivalry.

191
00:09:00,900 --> 00:09:01,530
Are you two

192
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:03,060
free tonight?

193
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:04,310
No.

194
00:09:04,670 --> 00:09:05,960
Go have fun without me.

195
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:09,820
That guy really hasn't changed one bit.

196
00:09:10,490 --> 00:09:11,950
Let's go, just the two of us.

197
00:09:11,950 --> 00:09:12,880
Okay.

198
00:09:33,310 --> 00:09:36,710
[Sound Wave Bar]

199
00:09:37,460 --> 00:09:39,670
-Please raise your glass.
-Okay.

200
00:09:40,580 --> 00:09:41,150
Then...

201
00:09:42,260 --> 00:09:45,520
-Looking forward to working with you!
-Likewise. Cheers.

202
00:09:48,520 --> 00:09:50,890
Ah.

203
00:09:51,210 --> 00:09:52,790
Still,

204
00:09:53,060 --> 00:09:56,260
even though you're busy,
you made time to hang out with me.

205
00:09:56,390 --> 00:09:58,220
That's what makes you so kind.

206
00:09:58,350 --> 00:10:01,220
We're more than just colleagues
who joined the same year—we're friends.

207
00:10:01,220 --> 00:10:02,700
Hey, you're making me fall for you.

208
00:10:02,700 --> 00:10:03,760
Alright, alright.

209
00:10:04,790 --> 00:10:05,920
Even so,

210
00:10:05,940 --> 00:10:08,040
you never contacted me at all, did you?

211
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:09,340
Neither did you.

212
00:10:10,390 --> 00:10:11,850
So,

213
00:10:12,290 --> 00:10:15,020
how does it feel
being back in Tokyo after so long?

214
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:17,800
Well,

215
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:21,210
the handover isn't done yet,
so it's hard to say.

216
00:10:21,350 --> 00:10:25,080
I'm still getting used to
the more aloof communication style here.

217
00:10:25,790 --> 00:10:28,350
The atmosphere with clients in Osaka
was completely different.

218
00:10:28,350 --> 00:10:29,170
Then

219
00:10:29,470 --> 00:10:31,800
maybe that place is more suitable for you?

220
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:34,630
Maybe.

221
00:10:35,510 --> 00:10:36,890
I came back...

222
00:10:38,420 --> 00:10:41,100
because I wanted to work with you.

223
00:10:44,180 --> 00:10:45,590
You're not even embarrassed saying that?

224
00:10:45,590 --> 00:10:46,810
I'm not paying the bill.

225
00:10:46,810 --> 00:10:47,470
Huh?

226
00:10:47,490 --> 00:10:48,780
I mean it.

227
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:50,150
Eh? Really?

228
00:10:50,280 --> 00:10:51,070
Why?

229
00:10:51,330 --> 00:10:52,430
I

230
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:54,460
worked really hard in Osaka, you know.

231
00:10:54,460 --> 00:10:55,540
I heard.

232
00:10:55,980 --> 00:10:57,280
Do you know why I worked so hard?

233
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:58,450
Well...

234
00:10:59,070 --> 00:11:00,130
Because of you two.

235
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:01,190
Huh?

236
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:04,230
You and Shido have been competing
with each other all this time,

237
00:11:04,230 --> 00:11:06,780
even though you're in different sections.

238
00:11:06,940 --> 00:11:09,710
We joined the company at the same time,
yet I was left on the sidelines.

239
00:11:09,710 --> 00:11:11,890
It really got to me.

240
00:11:11,920 --> 00:11:13,690
Oh, really?

241
00:11:13,710 --> 00:11:14,600
Sorry. That's on me.

242
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:15,610
I didn't mean to...

243
00:11:15,610 --> 00:11:17,050
Don't apologize.

244
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:19,500
I'm the one who chose to feel that way.

245
00:11:21,360 --> 00:11:22,900
Besides,

246
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:25,920
I trained hard in Osaka.

247
00:11:27,110 --> 00:11:29,760
All so I could join your rivalry.

248
00:11:29,780 --> 00:11:30,800
No.

249
00:11:30,820 --> 00:11:32,280
Even if you say so...

250
00:11:32,310 --> 00:11:33,710
I'm serious.

251
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:36,280
I

252
00:11:36,690 --> 00:11:38,710
have no intention of competing with you.

253
00:11:38,710 --> 00:11:39,740
Why?

254
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:41,010
"Why?"

255
00:11:41,520 --> 00:11:42,380
Because

256
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:45,740
that's a special way
of communicating between Shido and me.

257
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:47,280
No, I don't get it.

258
00:11:47,480 --> 00:11:48,350
What do you mean
by "way of communicating?"

259
00:11:48,350 --> 00:11:49,260
I mean,

260
00:11:49,490 --> 00:11:51,350
you and I are already friends, right?

261
00:11:51,350 --> 00:11:53,380
There's no need for us to compete.

262
00:11:54,670 --> 00:11:56,740
Hmm... I don't quite get it.

263
00:11:58,130 --> 00:11:59,240
But I understand.

264
00:11:59,270 --> 00:12:00,670
What exactly do you understand?

265
00:12:00,670 --> 00:12:02,620
In that case, I'll...

266
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:05,420
just compete with Shido.

267
00:12:05,440 --> 00:12:07,320
You didn't understand anything.

268
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:10,190
I can't force you if you don't want to.

269
00:12:10,530 --> 00:12:11,270
Besides,

270
00:12:11,490 --> 00:12:14,490
he's in the same section as me.
It's perfect.

271
00:12:14,510 --> 00:12:15,850
No, Zen...

272
00:12:17,490 --> 00:12:18,510
Shido

273
00:12:18,530 --> 00:12:20,530
won't accept the challenge either.

274
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:21,780
Really?

275
00:12:22,270 --> 00:12:22,700
Eh?

276
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:24,530
You've

277
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:29,110
only had drinks with me once.
You don't really know my abilities yet.

278
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:33,840
The day I become Shido's rival
isn't far off...

279
00:12:35,490 --> 00:12:36,350
-I think.
-Hmm.

280
00:12:42,190 --> 00:12:42,660
Oh?

281
00:12:43,390 --> 00:12:44,390
Not bad.

282
00:12:45,030 --> 00:12:46,500
Not bad. Oh!

283
00:12:46,680 --> 00:12:49,380
This is great! Down in one go!

284
00:12:49,410 --> 00:12:51,040
I'll drink too.

285
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:59,280
You sure put that beer away, didn't you?

286
00:12:59,520 --> 00:13:00,380
Not bad.

287
00:13:00,410 --> 00:13:01,210
Ah, excuse me,

288
00:13:01,210 --> 00:13:02,740
could we get another round?

289
00:13:02,750 --> 00:13:04,390
Draft beers, please.

290
00:13:04,620 --> 00:13:05,520
Thank you.

291
00:13:05,540 --> 00:13:06,230
Thank you.

292
00:13:06,250 --> 00:13:07,490
Thank you.

293
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:08,840
Looking forward to
working together from here on.

294
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:09,870
Likewise.

295
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,080
We're leaving now.

296
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:12,150
Excuse us.

297
00:13:19,110 --> 00:13:20,530
It's gotten pretty late.

298
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:21,350
Sorry about that.

299
00:13:21,350 --> 00:13:23,550
No, not at all. This was time well spent.

300
00:13:23,610 --> 00:13:26,120
I'm really happy
I got to work with you again, Mr. Shido.

301
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:27,210
Me too.

302
00:13:28,760 --> 00:13:31,460
Next time, let's invite Yotsuya
and have dinner together.

303
00:13:31,460 --> 00:13:32,190
Sounds good.

304
00:13:32,190 --> 00:13:32,920
Definitely.

305
00:13:33,420 --> 00:13:33,890
Ah.

306
00:13:34,470 --> 00:13:35,320
Speaking of which,

307
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:37,320
do you know a Futami at your company?

308
00:13:37,670 --> 00:13:40,240
Futami from the Osaka branch?

309
00:13:40,270 --> 00:13:41,210
Yeah, him.

310
00:13:41,480 --> 00:13:43,830
I heard he got transferred back.

311
00:13:44,760 --> 00:13:47,650
Mr. Mochida, you went to university
with Yotsuya and him, right?

312
00:13:47,650 --> 00:13:48,920
Yes.

313
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:50,420
When you think about it,

314
00:13:50,420 --> 00:13:53,160
I seem to have
quite a connection with your company.

315
00:13:53,160 --> 00:13:54,460
Indeed.

316
00:13:54,490 --> 00:13:55,300
Those two

317
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:57,330
seem to be having
a cohort get-together tonight.

318
00:13:57,330 --> 00:13:58,400
Seems like it.

319
00:13:59,060 --> 00:14:01,100
They're still as close as ever.

320
00:14:02,170 --> 00:14:03,810
Are they that close?

321
00:14:04,770 --> 00:14:07,630
At first, it was mostly
Futami clinging to Yotsuya.

322
00:14:07,700 --> 00:14:09,520
Then, it felt like Yotsuya
warmed up to him eventually.

323
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:10,450
Warmed up to him?

324
00:14:10,900 --> 00:14:13,560
Those two were together
all the time in college.

325
00:14:13,670 --> 00:14:16,190
They even went on a trip together,
just the two of them.

326
00:14:16,190 --> 00:14:17,550
A trip?

327
00:14:18,570 --> 00:14:20,250
Ah, speaking of which...

328
00:14:20,280 --> 00:14:22,280
The photos from back then...

329
00:14:22,740 --> 00:14:23,400
Ah.

330
00:14:23,780 --> 00:14:25,240
Futami just sent one over.

331
00:14:27,060 --> 00:14:28,640
What a coincidence.

332
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:29,850
Look.

333
00:14:30,920 --> 00:14:32,470
Yeah.

334
00:14:33,880 --> 00:14:36,990
This photo brings back memories.

335
00:14:41,570 --> 00:14:42,480
Haha.

336
00:15:03,340 --> 00:15:07,490
[Are you home yet?]

337
00:15:25,860 --> 00:15:26,320
Eh?

338
00:15:27,060 --> 00:15:27,730
Why?

339
00:15:29,140 --> 00:15:29,620
What?

340
00:15:33,850 --> 00:15:34,540
Eh?

341
00:15:35,230 --> 00:15:36,160
Why are you here?

342
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:37,690
I should be asking you that.

343
00:15:37,710 --> 00:15:38,280
Why are you here?

344
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:39,060
No.

345
00:15:39,090 --> 00:15:40,620
You're the one who should explain.

346
00:15:40,620 --> 00:15:42,160
Forget it.

347
00:15:44,790 --> 00:15:45,960
Come in.

348
00:15:49,330 --> 00:15:52,400
We got a little too carried away drinking.

349
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:54,890
He got pretty drunk,

350
00:15:54,910 --> 00:15:56,590
so I brought him back.

351
00:15:58,010 --> 00:15:58,740
Him?

352
00:15:58,770 --> 00:15:59,310
Yeah.

353
00:16:10,490 --> 00:16:10,840
Eh?

354
00:16:12,410 --> 00:16:13,070
So,

355
00:16:13,540 --> 00:16:14,800
why are you here?

356
00:16:15,990 --> 00:16:17,320
Yotsuya called me over.

357
00:16:17,590 --> 00:16:19,330
He said he was drinking with you.

358
00:16:19,330 --> 00:16:20,490
Oh, I see.

359
00:16:22,190 --> 00:16:24,280
Well, in that case,

360
00:16:24,850 --> 00:16:26,910
let's grab a drink, just the two of us.

361
00:16:27,070 --> 00:16:29,070
Haven't you had quite a bit already?

362
00:16:29,790 --> 00:16:32,070
That little bit of alcohol is nothing.

363
00:16:32,090 --> 00:16:33,440
I see.

364
00:16:33,670 --> 00:16:35,250
You've always been able to
hold your liquor.

365
00:16:35,250 --> 00:16:36,510
I'd almost forgotten.

366
00:16:38,410 --> 00:16:41,410
I bought a lot. There's still plenty left.

367
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:43,160
Well,

368
00:16:43,750 --> 00:16:45,690
he'll probably wake up soon anyway.

369
00:16:45,690 --> 00:16:47,000
Here.

370
00:16:47,240 --> 00:16:48,890
Then, just a little.

371
00:16:57,390 --> 00:16:59,440
Still, you really surprised me.

372
00:17:00,510 --> 00:17:02,410
You've become quite polished now.

373
00:17:02,410 --> 00:17:03,740
What makes you say that?

374
00:17:04,530 --> 00:17:07,790
Earlier today, I thought you were still
the same as before.

375
00:17:08,369 --> 00:17:11,450
But after work, you actually came
all the way over for drinks.

376
00:17:11,450 --> 00:17:13,380
The old you would've never done it.

377
00:17:14,150 --> 00:17:16,710
I'm just a bit more composed than before.

378
00:17:16,940 --> 00:17:17,660
Huh?

379
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:19,050
Composed, huh?

380
00:17:20,089 --> 00:17:22,290
The sales ace really is something else.

381
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:23,980
Don't keep provoking me.

382
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:26,329
But that composure of yours

383
00:17:26,420 --> 00:17:27,849
-will be gone soon.
-Hm?

384
00:17:29,490 --> 00:17:32,620
You mean that talk
about you wanting to join our rivalry?

385
00:17:33,230 --> 00:17:34,270
Yes.

386
00:17:34,550 --> 00:17:36,820
-You and me. Let's compete...
-I refuse.

387
00:17:37,160 --> 00:17:38,100
Why?

388
00:17:38,130 --> 00:17:40,560
If you want to compete, do it on your own.

389
00:17:40,590 --> 00:17:41,520
Huh?

390
00:17:41,990 --> 00:17:43,920
It takes two people to have a rivalry.

391
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:45,220
Anyway,

392
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:48,300
just dealing with Yotsuya
keeps me plenty busy as it is.

393
00:17:48,530 --> 00:17:49,520
You too, huh.

394
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:52,250
What do you mean?

395
00:17:53,010 --> 00:17:55,290
Yotsuya turned me down too.

396
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:57,270
I

397
00:17:57,760 --> 00:18:00,020
have no intention of competing with you.

398
00:18:00,140 --> 00:18:01,020
Of course.

399
00:18:01,050 --> 00:18:02,710
What do you mean, "of course?"

400
00:18:05,550 --> 00:18:06,500
By the way,

401
00:18:06,820 --> 00:18:08,950
why are you so set on competing with us?

402
00:18:10,180 --> 00:18:11,710
That's because

403
00:18:12,090 --> 00:18:15,680
I'm more suitable for Yotsuya than you.

404
00:18:18,420 --> 00:18:19,520
What?

405
00:18:19,940 --> 00:18:22,730
Where does that come from? Are you crazy?

406
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:24,040
You're drunk.

407
00:18:24,060 --> 00:18:24,600
Ah.

408
00:18:25,180 --> 00:18:27,560
I've been drinking.

409
00:18:27,670 --> 00:18:30,150
But I've been perfectly clear-headed
this whole time.

410
00:18:30,150 --> 00:18:32,080
What is that even supposed to mean?

411
00:18:33,530 --> 00:18:36,980
Every single thing you say
just gets on my nerves.

412
00:18:37,830 --> 00:18:39,370
Fine.

413
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:42,210
Then I'll just say it straight
while I have the chance.

414
00:18:42,210 --> 00:18:43,230
I've

415
00:18:43,260 --> 00:18:46,910
had a problem with you
since the day we joined this company.

416
00:18:47,180 --> 00:18:49,770
I don't care about
your little "high-school rival" story.

417
00:18:49,770 --> 00:18:52,290
But why does he only ever care about you?

418
00:18:52,310 --> 00:18:55,700
I'm the one who was by his side
throughout university.

419
00:18:55,730 --> 00:18:59,250
But why is he so fixated on someone

420
00:18:59,270 --> 00:19:02,460
as dull and prickly as you?

421
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:04,300
Give you an inch, and you just keep going,
don't you?

422
00:19:04,300 --> 00:19:07,340
What's wrong with telling the truth?

423
00:19:07,510 --> 00:19:08,990
And you?

424
00:19:09,020 --> 00:19:12,710
You've always looked at me
like I was a nuisance. So rude!

425
00:19:12,730 --> 00:19:15,610
You are a nuisance. And you keep
provoking me at every turn.

426
00:19:15,610 --> 00:19:19,770
And you always wear that calm expression,
looking down on me, huh?

427
00:19:20,190 --> 00:19:22,250
You're being paranoid.

428
00:19:22,270 --> 00:19:24,650
The moment you start thinking
you're being looked down on,

429
00:19:24,650 --> 00:19:27,660
you've already admitted your own failure.

430
00:19:29,460 --> 00:19:30,370
Ah!

431
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:31,490
You're so irritating.

432
00:19:31,490 --> 00:19:32,800
Fine. Let's settle this.

433
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:33,760
You're so persistent.

434
00:19:33,760 --> 00:19:36,120
Let's see which of us is
better suited to be his rival.

435
00:19:36,120 --> 00:19:37,710
His rival...

436
00:19:37,730 --> 00:19:38,870
It's you, right?

437
00:19:38,900 --> 00:19:40,770
For now, maybe.

438
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:43,150
But if I become
the top salesman in Section 2,

439
00:19:43,150 --> 00:19:45,680
he'll only pay attention to me.

440
00:19:45,700 --> 00:19:48,900
You think I'd just
hand first place over to you?

441
00:19:49,320 --> 00:19:51,340
Don't underestimate me.

442
00:19:51,370 --> 00:19:52,890
Understood.

443
00:19:53,310 --> 00:19:55,580
You've said your piece—
then I'll take you up on

444
00:19:55,580 --> 00:19:57,710
that challenge.

445
00:19:59,200 --> 00:19:59,780
Eh?

446
00:20:06,790 --> 00:20:07,240
Ah.

447
00:20:08,330 --> 00:20:09,750
What are you doing?

448
00:20:10,650 --> 00:20:12,270
Well...

449
00:20:12,300 --> 00:20:13,360
Zen, why are you...

450
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:15,290
Shido, why are you here?

451
00:20:19,110 --> 00:20:20,880
Oh, right!

452
00:20:20,910 --> 00:20:23,590
I called you! Sorry, sorry.

453
00:20:23,620 --> 00:20:27,110
I drank too much and passed out.

454
00:20:27,620 --> 00:20:28,840
More importantly,

455
00:20:28,860 --> 00:20:31,030
you seem awfully concerned about this guy.

456
00:20:31,030 --> 00:20:32,960
And he seems pretty happy about it.

457
00:20:33,710 --> 00:20:34,700
Are you listening?

458
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:35,940
I am listening.

459
00:20:35,990 --> 00:20:37,090
Happy?

460
00:20:37,120 --> 00:20:37,850
For what?

461
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:39,440
Competing with me.

462
00:20:39,890 --> 00:20:40,510
What?

463
00:20:40,870 --> 00:20:44,470
Well, whether it even counts as
a competition remains to be seen.

464
00:20:44,520 --> 00:20:46,960
Talking big, but secretly
terrified on the inside, aren't you?

465
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:49,120
I have no reason to get worked up.

466
00:20:49,870 --> 00:20:50,850
Whatever.

467
00:20:51,580 --> 00:20:52,900
I need a smoke.

468
00:20:53,090 --> 00:20:54,420
Go to the balcony!

469
00:20:55,020 --> 00:20:57,050
It's so hot outside.

470
00:20:57,070 --> 00:20:58,950
The balcony!

471
00:20:59,120 --> 00:21:00,720
Don't make me repeat myself.

472
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:16,300
That guy...

473
00:21:17,050 --> 00:21:18,650
is staying the night, right?

474
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:19,600
Yeah.

475
00:21:23,360 --> 00:21:25,110
He's really fond of you.

476
00:21:26,360 --> 00:21:27,680
Yeah.

477
00:21:27,970 --> 00:21:30,350
He's always been like that.

478
00:21:31,650 --> 00:21:32,340
Well...

479
00:21:33,390 --> 00:21:34,090
What?

480
00:21:35,870 --> 00:21:37,820
Are you suspecting something
between Futami and me?

481
00:21:37,820 --> 00:21:39,370
No.

482
00:21:40,250 --> 00:21:42,570
I know you're only interested in me.

483
00:21:46,380 --> 00:21:47,760
Then...

484
00:21:49,480 --> 00:21:50,680
Why did you come over?

485
00:21:52,850 --> 00:21:53,780
Do I need a reason

486
00:21:54,360 --> 00:21:55,540
to come see you?

487
00:21:59,370 --> 00:22:01,580
But I'm going home now.

488
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:05,410
Hey, Zen.

489
00:22:07,690 --> 00:22:08,890
Don't take

490
00:22:09,480 --> 00:22:11,140
what that guy said seriously.

491
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:12,050
Well,

492
00:22:12,690 --> 00:22:14,620
now that we're in the same section,

493
00:22:15,110 --> 00:22:17,010
there'll still be competition work-wise.

494
00:22:17,010 --> 00:22:17,800
Besides,

495
00:22:18,650 --> 00:22:22,510
I told you that competing with you
isn't interesting anymore, right?

496
00:22:22,520 --> 00:22:23,060
Eh?

497
00:22:27,870 --> 00:22:29,460
Then, see you at work.

498
00:22:35,970 --> 00:22:36,810
Ah.

499
00:22:38,810 --> 00:22:40,990
It's so hot.

500
00:22:42,890 --> 00:22:43,990
Where's Shido?

501
00:22:46,130 --> 00:22:47,140
He went back.

502
00:22:48,670 --> 00:22:51,030
What a heartless guy.

503
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:53,790
He could've at least said goodbye to me.

504
00:22:56,160 --> 00:22:57,180
What's wrong?

505
00:22:59,170 --> 00:22:59,740
Haha.

506
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:00,990
Nothing.

507
00:23:01,810 --> 00:23:02,970
Nothing's wrong.

508
00:23:04,490 --> 00:23:05,540
Yotsuya,

509
00:23:06,140 --> 00:23:07,930
let me stay here tonight.

510
00:23:08,670 --> 00:23:10,530
Going home is too much of a hassle.

511
00:23:16,110 --> 00:23:16,650
Okay.

512
00:23:18,560 --> 00:23:19,010
Oh.

513
00:24:57,480 --> 00:25:00,970
[In the Next Episode]

514
00:24:58,240 --> 00:25:01,150
The great me will be heading off first.

515
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:04,170
[Episode 8: How Should I Put It? Geez...]

516
00:25:01,180 --> 00:25:02,160
Why are you

517
00:25:02,190 --> 00:25:03,470
so obsessed with Yotsuya?

518
00:25:03,470 --> 00:25:04,610
I

519
00:25:04,640 --> 00:25:06,610
really respect Yotsuya.

520
00:25:06,890 --> 00:25:07,950
-Shut up.
-Shut up.

521
00:25:08,330 --> 00:25:09,190
I feel

522
00:25:09,220 --> 00:25:11,060
things have been tense lately

523
00:25:11,080 --> 00:25:12,230
between you and Mr. Futami.

524
00:25:12,230 --> 00:25:14,610
You actually have a cute side to you.

525
00:25:14,630 --> 00:25:15,150
Huh?

526
00:25:15,240 --> 00:25:16,120
I

527
00:25:16,150 --> 00:25:18,280
might want to get to know you better.

528
00:25:18,300 --> 00:25:19,800
I have them—friends.

529
00:25:19,830 --> 00:25:21,070
How rude.

530
00:25:21,090 --> 00:25:22,470
Can't I take Shido's place

531
00:25:22,470 --> 00:25:24,060
in your rivalry?

532
00:25:25,070 --> 00:25:27,390
I'm fine.

